      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI < 2% for all three QoIs; mesh convergence study with at least three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three structured hex-dominant meshes (coarse 0.8 mm, medium 0.5 mm, fine 0.3 mm element size at screw shank) were analysed. GCI values: stiffness 0.9%, yield force 1.4%, force at 40 mm 1.7%. All below 2% threshold. Discretization error level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Newton-Raphson residual norm < 1×10⁻⁵ at each load step; energy criterion < 1×10⁻⁴.",
      "rationale": "All analyses converged with force residual norm below 8×10⁻⁶ and energy criterion below 6×10⁻⁵. No diverged load steps across 11 model instances. Solver error level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions by a second qualified analyst not involved in model construction.",
      "rationale": "A second FDA OSEL engineer independently reviewed all boundary condition specifications, contact pair definitions, and material property assignments against the ASTM F1717 test fixture geometry. No discrepancies identified. Use error level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Nonlinear isotropic hardening plasticity (Ti-6Al-4V) with frictional contact (μ=0.2) selected based on published literature; model form uncertainty quantified via sensitivity study.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity was selected for the Ti-6Al-4V screw based on published tensile coupon data. Frictional contact (μ=0.2) was chosen consistent with tribological measurements in the literature. Sensitivity to μ (0.15–0.25) showed <3% QoI variation. Model form level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (E, σ_y, tangent modulus) sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon testing; geometric dimensions from CMM measurement of each test specimen.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield stress, and tangent modulus were derived from five tensile coupons machined from the same Ti-6Al-4V bar stock as the test screws. CMM measurements of each of the 11 constructs provided specimen-specific geometry inputs. Uncertainty in inputs propagated via Monte Carlo (n=1000). Model inputs level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 specimens from production lot with documented dimensional inspection; specimens distributed across two independent laboratories.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from a single production lot were tested — six at laboratory A and five at laboratory B. Each specimen received dimensional inspection per ASTM F1717 Section 7. Sample size exceeds the minimum N=10 threshold. Test samples level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two loading rates or two environmental conditions representative of the COU; environmental parameters logged throughout each test.",
      "rationale": "All bench tests were conducted at a single crosshead displacement rate (5 mm/min) and ambient laboratory conditions. Environmental parameters (temperature, humidity) were logged but only one loading rate was applied. This limits test condition coverage to gradation 2, below the required level 3. Risk accepted given the quasi-static nature of the clinical loading scenario."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and material parameters demonstrably traceable to measured experimental conditions; any deviations documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Each FEA instance used specimen-specific CMM geometry and lot-specific material properties. Fixture compliance was measured and incorporated as a linear spring boundary condition. Deviations between FEA inputs and experimental conditions were documented and shown to contribute <2% to QoI uncertainty. Equivalency level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percentage difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "For all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm), E/uval values were 0.87, 1.41, and 1.62 respectively — all below 1.96 — and percentage differences were 4.2%, 6.8%, and 7.5% — all below 10%. Acceptance criteria fully met. Output comparison level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly correspond to regulatory submission endpoints and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three primary endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and cited in FDA guidance for pedicle screw submissions. These QoIs directly relate to clinical failure modes (fatigue fracture and permanent deformation). Relevance level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments replicate the geometry, loading mode, and material system of the COU; any differences between validation and COU conditions are bounded.",
      "rationale": "The validation experiments used production-equivalent non-cannulated 7.5 mm screws assembled in ASTM F1717-compliant fixtures with the same polyacetal bone surrogate blocks as the COU. Loading mode (compression-bending) and fixture geometry are identical to the intended use scenario. Differences between validation and COU conditions are limited to the single-rate test condition noted under Test conditions. Relevance level 3 achieved."
    }
